Great local place.  Most folks get the pho but we loved the specialty dishes.   Hot and sour soup, clay pot fish and papaya salad all were DELICIOUS and reasonably priced.    Service was fast and friendly.   Ample parking and close to Waikiki make this a GREAT option for anyone trying to escape the tourist traps of Waikiki and enjoy authentic Vietnamese cuisine .

I live in Ewa, so when my friend said we had to try this place, I was praying the drive would be worth it. I'm happy to say it was! The pho broth and noodles were delicious. We also had the barbeque pork and shrimp summer rolls. The wait staff was friendly, and we didn't wait too long for food to be served. Prices were pretty reasonable. For 3 bowls of pho (1 large, 2 medium), 2 iced Vietnamese iced teas, and an order of barbecue pork and shrimp summer rolls we paid about $41. The parking garage is located off South Beretania. I'll definitely be coming back!

The only thing saving this place from a 2star review is the friendly fast service.

Excellent pho, with strong flavor in the broth (since the meat soup bowls come with plenty of meat to add to the flavor), and all of the typical fixings.  The fried spring rolls have a hearty amount of minced meat, for a meat lovers like me!  They also serve on green vegetables... Ong Choi is my favorite and they serve it perfectly (I've had it by itself with garlic and with beef and both were great)!  Very clean, modern and basic decor, and never too crowded.  Definitely a safe go to place for phone and more.
